<p>The <strong>$50-100 tier</strong> reveals premium single-vineyard bottlings from renowned estates like Pride Mountain or Leonetti Cellar, showcasing complex layers of dark fruit, espresso, and mineral undertones. <strong>Above $100</strong>, you enter the realm of cult producers like Screaming Eagle or Château Le Pin, where exceptional vineyard sites and meticulous winemaking create collectible wines with decades of aging potential.</p>

