<p>Avoid vague terms like "Cellared and Bottled by"—instead, prioritize "Produced and Bottled by" which ensures the winery made the wine. <strong>Alcohol levels between 13.5-14.5%</strong> typically indicate balanced ripeness without excessive extraction.</p>

